    "body": "Not being a rust programmer, I take didn't think about this. Forgive me for my naivety, I'm sure I'm about to make it more apparent lol\r\n\r\n`curl https://sh.rustup.rs -sSf | sh` gives an error about replacing rust so I didn't verify the solution. \r\n\r\n```zsh\r\n$ rustc --version\r\nrustc 1.70.0 (90c541806 2023-05-31) (built from source tarball)\r\n$ cargo --version\r\ncargo 1.70.0\r\n```\r\n`rustc` and `cargo` have that version. The `apt` package does not build `rustup` and this is what I get from `apt install cargo`. I suspect this will be a common method for installation. \r\n\r\nLet me know if there is more info I can provide that would be helpful.",
